Half, 
forming a half (divided into 2 parts);
{#arDa-arDa#} the one half-the other half.

{@--1@} A half,
half portion; {#sarvanASe samutpanne arDaM#} 
{#tyajati paMqitaH; gatamarDaM divasasya#} <ls>V. 2</ls>;  
{#pUrvArDaH#} first half; so {#uttara°#} latter half;
{#dakziRa°#} southern half (half on the
right side); so {#jaGana°, avara°, para°#},
{#grAma°#} &c.; {#yadarDe vicCinnaM#} <ls>Ś. 1. 9</ls> 
divided in half; {#fjvAyatArDaM#} <ls>M. 27</ls>;  
<ls>R. 3. 59</ls>, <ls n="R.">12. 99</ls>; {#rAtrO tadarDaM gataM#} <ls>Bh. 3. 107</ls>; one
part of two, apart, partly (<ab>Ved.</ab>);
{@--2@} Nearness, proximity; see {#arDadeva#}.
{#arDa#} may be compounded with
almost every noun and adjective;
as first member of compound
with nouns it means ‘a half of’,
and forms an {#ekadoSisamAsa#} or {#tatpuruza#};
{#°kAyaH#} = {#arDaM kAyasya#}; {#°pippalI, °mArgaH#};
{#°puruzaH#} &c.; with adjectives, it has an
adverbial force; {#°SyAma#} half dark;
{#°Bukta#} half eaten; so {#°pizwa, °pUrRa#} &c.;
with numeral adjectives it may
mean either ‘a half of’ or ‘with an
additional half’; {#°SataM#} half of 100 {%<ab>i. e.</ab>%}
50; or {#arDena sahitaM SataM#} {%<ab>i. e.</ab>%} 150; with
ordinal numerals ‘with a half of that 

number;’ {#°tftIyaM#} containing two and
the third only half; {%<ab>i. e.</ab>%} two and a
half; so {#°caturTa#} three and a half.

